Interface ResettableIterator

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Iterator
    All Known Subinterfaces:

    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ArrayIterator, ArrayListIterator, EmptyIterator, EmptyListIterator, EmptyMapIterator, EmptyOrderedIterator, EmptyOrderedMapIterator, EntrySetMapIterator, ListIteratorWrapper, LoopingIterator, LoopingListIterator, ObjectArrayIterator, ObjectArrayListIterator, ReverseListIterator, SingletonIterator, SingletonListIterator
    @Deprecated(since="2021-04-30")
public interface ResettableIterator
extends Iterator
    Deprecated.
    Commons Collections 3 is in maintenance mode. Commons Collections 4 should be used instead.
    Defines an iterator that can be reset back to an initial state.

    This interface allows an iterator to be repeatedly reused.

    Since:
    Commons Collections 3.0
